<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>

<p>Fragments of <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">architrave</rs> blocks (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">1.63</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.31</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.57</measure>-<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.69</measure> in depth) from the entablature of the north portico of the Sebasteion. Above is a decoration of <rs type="decoration">mutule</rs>s, spaced at intervals of  <measure dim="none" type="length" unit="metre" precision="circa">0.30</measure>.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text"><head>Description of Text</head><p>The <rs type="execution" key="scalpro">inscription</rs> runs in one line on a single, unstepped, face. The face is drafted above, below and at the ends of each block; the upper drafting line rises to follow the line of the moulding between the mutules.  The inscription was cut when the blocks were in place, and letters run across joins.</p>
</div><div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p> <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.09</measure>; small star for stop.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date exact="none" notAfter="0100" notBefore="0014"> First century A.D.</date></p>
</div>
